protein.specific_function: Flavoprotein (FP) subunit of succinate dehydrogenase (SDH) that is involved in complex II of the mitochondrial electron transport chain and is responsible for transferring electrons from succinate to ubiquinone (coenzyme Q). Can act as a tumor suppressor.

go_class.description: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the ch-ch group of donors
generation of precursor metabolites and energy
